  "title": "Implement windowing to avoid render elements not on the screen",
  "body": "Let's do a POC at implementing lazyload: true on the hits widget, it should then only render react hits elements when they are visible, with an offset (so that if you start scrolling, you already see some).\n\nMultiple libraries are already either doing windowing or tracking dom nodes position inside the window. Let's try to use them.\n",
